## Critical Dependency Rules

- `api-gateway` **must** use `spring-boot-starter-webflux` and `spring-cloud-starter-gateway-server-webflux`. Never add `spring-boot-starter-web` to the gateway module.
- All other services use `spring-boot-starter-web` (servlet stack).
- Always declare dependency versions in the root `pom.xml` `<dependencyManagement>` block; never hardcode versions in module POMs.
- The shared `common-core`, `common-web`, and `common-persistence` modules are plain JARs (no `spring-boot-maven-plugin` repackage); all other service modules are executable Spring Boot fat JARs.
- `common-core` must never depend on `spring-boot-starter-web`/`webflux` or JPA, so it can be consumed by both servlet services and the reactive `api-gateway`.
- Servlet microservices depend on `common-web` and `common-persistence` (both transitively include `common-core`). The `api-gateway` may depend only on `common-core` — never on `common-web` or `common-persistence` (their servlet/JPA deps would break the reactive gateway).
- Annotation processors (MapStruct, Lombok) must be declared in `<annotationProcessorPaths>` of `maven-compiler-plugin`, not as regular dependencies.
